{
	"info": {
		"_postman_id": "965e2da3-e7f9-4e6e-9824-08a8325c7ac9",
		"name": "Enhanced Face Recognition API",
		"description": "# 🎯 Enhanced Face Recognition API Collection\n\nStreamlined collection for multi-tenant face recognition system with enhanced features:\n\n## 🔧 **Core Features**\n- **Enhanced Registration**: Multi-app face registration with aliases\n- **Enhanced Identification**: Best match per person logic\n- **Face Management**: Person and face lifecycle management\n- **Multi-App Support**: Application-level isolation\n- **Database Management**: Stats and record cleanup\n\n## 🆕 **Enhanced Capabilities**\n- **Multiple Faces per Person**: Register multiple photos per individual\n- **Application Isolation**: Separate face databases per app (app_id)\n- **Face Aliases**: Descriptive names (\"profile_photo\", \"id_document\")\n- **Primary Face Management**: Designate best representative face\n- **Best Match Logic**: One result per person (no duplicates)\n\n## 📥 **Input Methods**\nAll endpoints support:\n1. **File Upload** (multipart/form-data)\n2. **Base64 Image** (JSON with `image_base64`)\n\n## 🏗️ **Architecture**\n- **Backend**: Flask with PostgreSQL + pgvector\n- **Face Models**: FaceNet with FAISS indexing\n- **Multi-Tenancy**: App-level data isolation\n- **Performance**: Optimized for multiple face scenarios\n\n## 🚀 **Getting Started**\n1. Set the `base_url` variable to your API endpoint\n2. Test the `/health` endpoint\n3. Register faces with `app_id` using enhanced registration\n4. Use enhanced identification for best match results\n5. Manage faces with person/face management endpoints\n\n## 🔐 **Response Format**\n```json\n{\n  \"success\": true/false,\n  \"app_id\": \"your_app_id\",\n  \"data\": {...},\n  \"processing_time\": 0.25\n}\n```",
		"schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
		"_exporter_id": "7577488"
	},
